            "created_at": "2018-01-28T22:59:27Z",
            "updated_at": "2018-01-28T22:59:27Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Should we have a policy in the future of updating to the latest dependencies before each release? Or should we remove version information and instead say \"you may be able to use older versions, but we don't guarantee it.\" The former keeps all the projects moving forward and I'd prefer it, but the later is more forgiving, especially if there's no actual incompatibility."
        },
        {
