            "created_at": "2018-01-29T19:19:36Z",
            "updated_at": "2018-01-29T19:19:36Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> you may be able to use older versions, but we don't guarantee it.\r\n\r\nI have a slight preference for this. At my day job, a (bad) decision was made long ago to run everything under a single global shared venv...  we are in the middle of a multi-year migration to fix that, but in the meantime it'd be nice to not have our hands tied on an old flask version just because we can't upgrade a few of the dependencies.\r\n\r\nThat said, it feels dangerous to fully remove versions... I would still leave minimum requirements in `setup.py` to prevent installing versions that are _already_ known to break.\r\n\r\nWhat about adding something to the docs like:\r\n> We only develop/test with the latest stable versions of our dependencies. You may be able to use older versions, but we don't guarantee it. If you find a version incompatibility, please file an issue on our GitHub repo so that we can bump the minimum required version for that dependency.\r\n\r\nAnd then also bump the dependencies to latest in `tox.ini`?\r\n\r\n"
        },
        {
