            "created_at": "2018-01-30T15:43:12Z",
            "updated_at": "2018-01-30T15:43:12Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I'm worried that a discrepancy between what we test in tox and what we list in setup.py would cause confusion.\r\n\r\nIf I bump all versions in setup.py, it means everyone is forced to use the latest versions at the time of release, which makes it easier for us instead of having to worry about compat checks. This makes it difficult for projects like yours to update, especially if there's no actual reason that a newer version is needed.\r\n\r\nIf I remove version information completely, `pip install -U flask` would update all the dependencies too, without forcing everything, but would make no guarantees about older supported versions. Which leaves projects like yours in the same difficult spot, because now, for example, you have to use Werkzeug 0.14 anyway because the session relies on a cookie feature introduced in that version.\r\n\r\nSo either I say \"you have to update\", or \"you don't have to update, but it's going to break anyways.\""
        },
