            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "If we use latest versions, then what releases do we update on? Major releases haven't exactly had the best schedule so far, so we'd be in sort of the same situation eventually. And do we pin to the absolute latest (`>=0.14.1`) or a more general version (`>=0.14`)?\r\n\r\nIf we keep minimum versions that aren't the latest versions, then what's the policy for changing them? Are we obligated to keep compat checks in for a year, then remember to remove them? Maintaining a list of minimum versions doesn't really guarantee anything, since we could change that minimum at any time anyway. It just means we have to keep testing what we say is the minimum, to make sure it's still the minimum."
        },
